---

Preheat oven 400 degrees. Cut the @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch cubes. Place
them in a #pot{} and cover with water. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch}, bring to boil,
and cook for ~{15-20%minutes}, until easily pierced with a knife.

Meanwhile, place the @chicken breasts{2} on a #baking sheet{}. Drizzle each with
@olive oil{1%teaspoon} and flip to coat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} on both sides.

In a #bowl{}, combine @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup},
@olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Top each chicken breast with the panko
topping and press to adhere. Place in the oven and roast for ~{12-14%minutes}, until
juices run clear when pierced.

While the chicken roasts, halve the @grape tomatoes{1%bunch}. Mince the
@garlic{2%cloves}. Thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate.

Toss the tomatoes with garlic, @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, scallion whites and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on the baking sheet next to the chicken and roast
for ~{6-8%minutes}, until softened.

> Remove the tomatoes from the sheet when they're done and place the chicken under the
> broiler to get a nice golden brown color!

Once the potatoes are done, drain and place in a bowl. Toss with scallion greens,
@olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and @balsamic vinegar{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Serve the chicken breast with the roasted tomatoes and potato salad to the side.